fr.inria.atlanmod.mogwai.transformation.atl.helper.blueprints

Class InPlaceBlueprintsTransformationHelper

  • Object
    • AbstractATLTransformationHelper<E,E>
      • InPlaceATLTransformationHelper<Vertex>
        • InPlaceBlueprintsTransformationHelper

  • public class InPlaceBlueprintsTransformationHelper
extends InPlaceATLTransformationHelper<Vertex>
    A blueprints-based InPlaceATLTransformationHelper that computes model transformations inside a blueprints database, storing the result aside the input model.

    Transformation-related elements, such as trace links and proxy links, are stored within the database, reducing the memory footprint compared to in-memory helpers.

    Author:
    Gwendal DANIEL
    See Also:
    InPlaceATLTransformationHelper

      • isTargetElement

        protected boolean isTargetElement(Vertex element)
        Checks if the provided element is in the target model.

        This method is specific to InPlaceATLTransformationHelper that uses the same ModelDatastore for source and target models. The transformation has to check if an element is in the target model in order to create concrete/proxy links and resolve elements.

        Specified by:
        isTargetElement in class InPlaceATLTransformationHelper<Vertex>
        Parameters:

        Returns:

      • createProxyLink

        protected void createProxyLink(Vertex from,
                               Vertex to,
                               String label,
                               String oppositeLabel,
                               boolean isContainment)
        Creates a proxy link between from and to.

        This method is similar to AbstractATLTransformationHelper.linkReference(Object, Object, String, String, boolean) with a to element in the source model. It creates an cross-model proxy link which is not defined in the source or target ModelDatastore that link the target element from to the source one to.

        Specified by:
        createProxyLink in class AbstractATLTransformationHelper<Vertex,Vertex>
        Parameters:
        from - the tail (in the target model) of the proxy link to create
        to - the head (in the source model) of the link to create
        label - the label of the proxy link to create
        oppositeLabel - the label of the opposite reference if it exists
        isContainment - true if the reference is a containment, false otherwise
        See Also:
        AbstractATLTransformationHelper.linkReference(Object, Object, String, String, boolean), AbstractATLTransformationHelper.linkReference(Object, Iterable, String, String, boolean)

      • createConcreteLink

        protected void createConcreteLink(Vertex from,
                                  Vertex to,
                                  String label,
                                  String oppositeLabel,
                                  boolean isContainment)
        Creates a concrete link between from and to.

        This method is similar to AbstractATLTransformationHelper.linkReference(Object, Object, String, String, boolean) with a to element in the target model. It creates a concrete mapped reference in the target model between the two elements from and to by using the internal target ModelDatastore.

        The default implementation of this method delegates the reference creation to the underlying target ModelDatastore. It can be extended to add transformation specific behavior.

        Overrides:
        createConcreteLink in class AbstractATLTransformationHelper<Vertex,Vertex>
        Parameters:
        from - the tail (in the target model) of the link to create
        to - the head (in the target model) of the link to create
        label - the label of the link to create
        oppositeLabel - the label of the opposite reference if it exists
        isContainment - true if the reference is a containment, false otherwise
        See Also:
        AbstractATLTransformationHelper.linkReference(Object, Object, String, String, boolean), AbstractATLTransformationHelper.linkReference(Object, Iterable, String, String, boolean)

      • resolveProxies

        public void resolveProxies(Vertex sourceProxy,
                           Vertex targetElement)
        Resolves the proxy links connected to sourceProxy by setting their tail to targetElement.

        sourceProxy is an element of the source model that has been transformed and is connected by proxy links to targetElement. Resolving a proxy removes the cross-model proxy links and replaces them by the corresponding link in the target model.

        Specified by:
        resolveProxies in class AbstractATLTransformationHelper<Vertex,Vertex>
        Parameters:
        sourceProxy - the element that is connected to proxy links
        targetElement - the element that resolves the proxies

      • resolve

        public Vertex resolve(Vertex sourceProxy)
        Resolves the sourceProxy element by retrieving the corresponding target element.

        This method returns an element of the target model that corresponds to the provided sourceProxy. Note that sourceProxy may not be resolvable if the corresponding target element hasn't been created yet (see AbstractATLTransformationHelper.isResolvable(Object)).

        Specified by:
        resolve in class AbstractATLTransformationHelper<Vertex,Vertex>
        Parameters:
        sourceProxy - the source element to resolve
        Returns:
        the target element corresponding to sourceProxy if it exists
